   "body" : "Add a check for the PoW's validity to `AcceptBlockHeader`, and disable the check during `LoadBlockIndex`.  Previously, if a peer sends headers with invalid PoW, they would be accepted to the on-disk block index, but then loading it on the next start would fail.\n\nNot sure if the proposed patch is the perfect solution.  Maybe the check in `LoadBlockIndex` should stay and just the one in `AcceptBlockHeader` be added?\n",
